![episode142.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1599050008358-P46XUKVXQKL6TRZMFAXB/episode142.jpg)

Unwatchable. Franchise Killers. The Worst of The Worst. These are the words used to describe two films that are largely panned by your modern comic book fan. Before the days of the MCU or DC's Cinematic Multiverse two films managed to damage any chances of a future for their potential franchises. That's right folk in this edition of Which WAS Worse, we argue which is actually the poorer film Superman IV: A Quest For Peace or Batman And Robin. It's a no holds barred debate with a clear winner so don't hesitate! Listen now**!**

**Please** leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
